node.text:
Oh man, it doesn't happen often that @jasperiuss feels like he just got started with the conversation and BAM an hour is over🤯

@alex_dorr is such an energetic, humble, charismatic, simply amazing human being. (He's also really handsome 😜) His love for fungi goes through all of our systems, is incredibly infectious and it feels like he has unlimited amounts to give. You do not want to miss this one!🔥

I am so humbled to receive such high praise from someone I hold in such high regard, although I know we're all incredibly busy, i know there will be some collaborations in the air.🪶🪶🪶 

FOLLOW: @alex_dorr & @mushroomrevival 

Stay Shroomie🍄💕

node.title: Humans, Mushrooms and Magic with @alex_dorr from @mushroomrevival

node.text:
Join us on @charlesrootz his beautiful 298 year old family house!

Charles is a professional musician with @rootzunderground and has recently co-founded a mushroom chocolate company @patoochocolate 🔥

Charles is an all round amazing person and his passion for mushrooms and music just oozes from him. He's been generous with his time, his words and his presence during my (@jasperiuss) trip through Jamaica. 🇯🇲

These are the leaders we need in the up and coming psychedelic space. Let's all learn from his caution and epic stories❤️🍄🙌

node.title: 🍄🍫 Mushroom Chocolate, Music and Accessibility with @charlesrootz

“We know that every particle in the physical universe takes its characteristics from the pitch and pattern and overtones or it’s particular frequency, it’s singing.
Before we make music, music makes us.” -Hazrat Inayat Khan 

Today our very own Chief Creative Officer Holden Davies of @nido_films was joined by @davidsatori from @dirtwire to discuss their influence of mushrooms for their creation of Music 🎶

If you are inspired by music & mushroom, tune into this conversation all about plant medicine & the healing power of music!
.
.
.

Join Skye from @real_mushrooms and yours truly, @jasperiuss for a deep dive into the world of medicinal mushrooms.🍄

Skye is one of the most knowledgeable people I've had the pleasure to talk to. He generously shared what he knows about polysaccharides, triterpenes, beta-glucans and all other mushroom medicines that our Fungi allies create to nurture our bodies.💪

Skye shares his story of growing up into a mycophelic family, how he reconnected with his father's fungal vision after rediscovering the healing powers of medicinal mushrooms in his late twenties.💫

We finished with talking about new up and coming mushrooms like Phellinus linteus and Lignosus rhinocerus.🌌

follow @real_mushrooms everywhere you consume media for more medicinal Mushroom knowledge🙌
.

node.text:
A key lesson we as humans can learn from Mushrooms: in a healthy environment, a healthy fungi is living in. In a healthy environment, a healthy human being is living in 💫

We are grateful for all the wisdom from our fungal allies and for Oliver paving the pathway for us to continue to harvest the knowledge from the mushrooms and share with the world 🌏

It is our goal to make fungal education fun, easy-to-learn, and accessible!

We have some exciting things to share with you all on the horizon…🤗

In the meantime, celebrate our Sacred Mycology School anniversary and take 50% off all our online courses!

Sign up now in our @fungiacademy bio 🍄
.
.
.

Oh man, it doesn't happen often that @jasperiuss feels like he just got started with the conversation and BAM an hour is over🤯

@alex_dorr is such an energetic, humble, charismatic, simply amazing human being. (He's also really handsome 😜) His love for fungi goes through all of our systems, is incredibly infectious and it feels like he has unlimited amounts to give. You do not want to miss this one!🔥

I am so humbled to receive such high praise from someone I hold in such high regard, although I know we're all incredibly busy, i know there will be some collaborations in the air.🪶🪶🪶 

FOLLOW: @alex_dorr & @mushroomrevival 

Stay Shroomie🍄💕

One year later… what a journey! #HappyAnniversary 🎉

Exactly one year ago we launched our online Sacred Mycology School 🙌

It was during a time when the world went in complete lockdown and we were unable to teach our in-person courses anymore, which was the main source of our income. The day we opened up our doors to presale the course our electricity was shut off and we managed to get it back on with the help of our first few students in our Sacred Mycology School, so thank you fungi fam! 🙏

“It was divine timing” Oliver would say. And it truly was. 💫

The world needed this now more than ever. To be able to learn how to safely grow, use, and integrate all kinds of mushrooms in the comfort of their homes; whether that be for medicinal benefits, edibility consumption, psychedelic exploration, or environment restoration.

In honor of our anniversary we want to gift our community 50% off all our Sacred Mycology Courses! 🔥

Start your journey now, link in our @fungiacademy bio! 🍄

node.text:
Want to give your crush a bouquet of your homegrown mushroom flush? 🤗

Oyster Mushrooms (Pleurotus Ostreatus) are a newbie grower's best friend when it comes to cultivation. They are one of the easiest mushrooms to grow as they can enjoy a wide variety of substrates like corn cobs, sawdust, coffee grounds, straw, cardboard, and many others! 🌿

These edible mushrooms are not just delicious edible mushrooms but do wonders for your health. Oyster Mushrooms are rich in protein, vitamin C, and potassium. They also can support the immune system, blood sugar regulation, cardiovascular conditions, skin problems, and brain health. 

🍄 Fungi Facts 🍄 Was first cultivated in Germany to help feed people during World World I. It received its name "Oyster Mushroom" due to the fact that the caps look like oysters (as you can tell from this photo from @freshcapmushrooms! 🦪

Want to learn how to grow your own Oyster Mushrooms? Click the link in our @fungiacademy bio to sign up for our newsletter 💌 
We have some exciting news releasing tomorrow so you can start growing mushrooms with a shweeet deal! 💫

node.text:
The Dawn of the Mushroom 🍄

We're living in a fungal renaissance. Our fungal allies are uncovering themselves from the underground, like they always have.

Even if we make life incredibly difficult on this planet for us, and most other living organisms. Fungi will thrive, they will rebuilt and with enough time, life will flourish. 

However, this is not what the fungi desire, they thrive in a world that is abundant and full of other organisms. Right now, they are coming out of the underground to support us in maintaining this abundance that we experience on this planet.

Let's not be blind, let's accept their generous support, embrace our alliance with these organisms and work hard on let's not disrupt the Holocene, the beautiful consistent time that has gotten us to where we are now. Not for the Fungi, they will be fine in the long run. They have proven it by surviving all major mass extinctions, they will do it again.

Let's embrace their support for us, our brothers and sisters, our daughters and sons.

Magic re sized

framed for a grey square 
Made to be scalable 
Distribution for the insaciable 
An infinite repeat 
A circle complete

the roots break free
The concrete cracks
Empires fall

Castles of sand 
Dissolve in one single
uttered breath
Dark matter births color 
From dust to dust 
We dance
And all the time 
Behind the curtain
The truth awaits
The illusion is your own
To create.

A new kind of Pie, Mushroom Pie 🍄 

Often we seek validation for deeper connections to spirit through ceremony in front of a fire, with a shaman, and entheogens... while forgetting that spirit is right in front of us every day with our relationship with food. 🙏

How often do you take time to make your food a ritual?

A Sacred Mycology immersion for the creative, eco-changemaker wanting to cultivate a deeper connection to the ancient organisms around us. 🍄

Our 6-Day Mushroom Cultivation course is finally back! 🚀

It is time to learn, grow, and thrive in an environment where we are surrounded by like-minded mycophiles from all over the world, where we can learn as a community about mushroom cultivation and the wondrous world of ecology.

✅ Learn how to grow, harvest, and store your home-grown mushrooms.🍄
✅ Discover our deep connection to the Fungal Queendom.👑
✅ Understand how to easily create a mushroom growing environment anywhere in the world.🌍
✅ Practice with the pros to start growing your mushrooms with confidence.🧬
✅ A week of Connection, Fun, and Fungal Education🎓

There are limited spaces available for our upcoming courses in Lake Atitlan, Guatemala.

October 17-23
December 5-11 
January 8-14

Visit our @fungiacademy link in bio for more details and to apply!

node.text:
Your Psychedelic Ancestors 💫

With the Psychedelic Renaissance being in full force, so many people are looking forward. Sometimes the best thing to do when one wants to move forward is to look back for a moment, and integrate the lessons from the ones that came before us. ⏳

This Thursday, July 29th, we will be co-hosting a webinar with @julian.vayne 💫

In this webinar Julian Vayne will guide participants through the long strange trip of psychedelic history.
​

How do lunar cycles influence the cycles of fungi? 

Considering the fact that lunar gravity influences every being on this planet, especially water bodies and those with water-based bodies (most of life), and considering the fact that most mushrooms are > 90% water… it’s almost certain that the moons influences plays SOME role in fungal fruitings, behaviors and expressions. 

Many Indigenous cultures that have deeply rooted ethnomycological history, especially those of the northern hemisphere in Scandinavia and Siberia, claim that fruitings of ground-dwelling, fleshy macrofungi occur in greater abundance on the full moon.

Since the moons gravity pulls the terrestrial tides (ground water) further up to the surface of the soil on full moons and even more so on new moons, it would make sense that lunar events have a direct effect on fruiting of certain species. 

But for now the exact knowing of these influences stays happily shrouded in mystery.
What the moons exact role is in fungal cycles, we just don’t really know. 
And maybe we’ll never know.
And that’s okay. 
~ 

Here is a rendition of the basic life cycle of a basidiomycete mushroom cycling with the lunar phases.
From my perspective, I’ve matched the different energetic expressions of the mushroom life cycle with the associated energetic expressions of the lunar cycle. 
From full; the biggest, boldest, brightest expression of the mature, sporulating fruiting body, to new; the deep, dark inquisitive phase of underground, rhizospheric mycelial navigation, and back again. 

In the center is the Elder Futhark Norse Rune, Inguz. The Elder Futhark runic alphabet is said to be the most ancient form of the many Indigenous writing systems from my Scandinavian ancestral lineages(s). Inguz or “the God, Ing” is the rune of fertility and new beginnings, marking a new phase of life. Also interpreted as a seed, the birthing of a new idea or life form. The shape also represents a doorway, the portal to the astral planes.
